    "body": "### Description\n\nUsing Neovim v0.11.1, `vim.opt.fileencoding` is `utf-8`.\n\nSteps to reproduce:\n1. Put a non-ascii character in string literal\n```c\n#include <stdio.h>\nint main() {\n  printf(\"•a\"); // U+2022 bullet Unicode character\n}\n```\n2. Delete that character\n```c\n#include <stdio.h>\nint main() {\n  printf(\"a\");\n}\n```\n3. clangd emits a warning message: \"Illegal character encoding in string literal\", it disappears when closing and reopening buffer\n\n\nWorkaround: setting `capabilities.offsetEncoding` to empty table fixes this issue.\n``` lua\nvim.lsp.config.clangd = {\n  capabilities = {\n    offsetEncoding = {},\n  },\n}\n```",
