            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Minimal reproducible configuration:\n```\nnvim\n├── init.lua\n└── lsp\n    └── clangd.lua\n```\n\n`clangd.lua` is copied from https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/562487bc108bf73c2493f9e701b9334b48163216/lsp/clangd.lua\n\n`init.lua` content:\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config { virtual_text = { spacing = 2 } }\nvim.lsp.enable(\"clangd\")\n```\n\nFollow the three steps described above to get a warning diagnostic from clangd: \"Illegal character encoding in string literal\".\n\nThe issue happens with Neovim v0.11.1 and Neovim 0.12.0 079e7d2b11\n\n> In any case, I don't see how this is a \"config\" issue. If it's an issue with Nvim, then it would be related to the Nvim lsp module in core.\n\nThis may be a config issue because it happens with clangd only, though it needs further investigation.",
